  <refnamediv>
    <refname>dctrl2xml</refname>
    <refpurpose>a Debian package control file to XML converter</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>&dhpackage;</command>
      <arg><replaceable>options</replaceable></arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>OPTIONS</title>
    <para>For a full summary of options, run <command>dctrl2xml 
      --help</command>.</para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-h, --help</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Show help about options.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-fFILE, --file=FILE</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Read Debian control structure from file 
            <replaceable>FILE</replaceable>.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>
  
  <refsect1>
    <title>EXAMPLES</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>apt-cache show hello build-essential | dctrl2xml</term>
        <listitem>
          <para><command>dctrl2xml</command> can be used in pipes. This
            example outputs an XML representation of the package records of
            the hello and build-essential packages to standard output.</para>
          <para>You can also use <command>apt-cache showsrc</command> to
            output an XML representation of source package records.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
       <term>apt-cache show hello | dctrl2xml | xmllint --format -</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>In this example the program <command>xmllint</command> is used
            to reformat and reindent <command>dctrl2xml</command>'s output to
            make the XML more human readable. <command>xmllint</command> is
            part of the Debian package libxml2-utils.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>
  
